    readTime: '7 min read',
    content: [
      '<h2>Finding the Good Ones (Without the Guesswork)</h2><p>Choosing a pool cleaning company starts with research. Check Google and Yelp reviews, paying attention to how companies respond to negative feedback. Ask neighbors with well-maintained pools for recommendations and look for certifications like Certified Pool & Spa Operator (CPO). Proper pool maintenance requires 3\u20135 hours every week of work, making professional selection crucial for protecting your investment and keeping swimmers safe.</p>',
      '<h2>Experience That Shows (Not Just Claims)</h2><p>Companies with years of experience have encountered every pool nightmare imaginable. Experienced providers understand different pool types (saltwater vs. chlorine) and can explain technical concepts in understandable language. Look for a company that demonstrates practical knowledge, not just marketing claims.</p>',
      '<h2>Services That Actually Matter</h2><p>Proper service includes skimming debris, vacuuming the floor, brushing walls and tiles, and chemical balancing. The best companies inspect equipment during visits and offer solutions for special issues like <a href="/resources/how-to-prevent-algae-growth-in-your-pool/">algae bloom</a>s. Make sure you understand exactly what\'s included in their service package before committing.</p>',
      '<h2>Communication That Actually Works</h2><p>Companies should respond within 24 hours and provide updates after each visit. Having the same technician service your pool consistently builds familiarity with your pool\'s specific needs and history, leading to better service outcomes.</p>',
      '<h2>Pricing That Makes Sense</h2><p>Most residential pools cost $85\u2013$150 per visit depending on size and features. Be wary of contracts with hefty cancellation fees, and note that some companies include perks like minor repairs in their service packages. Extremely low prices often indicate cut corners or hidden costs.</p>',
      '<h2>Protection When Things Go Sideways</h2><p>Companies should carry liability insurance and offer satisfaction guarantees. Some provide warranties against common issues like algae blooms. Always verify insurance coverage before hiring\u2014it protects you from liability if something goes wrong during service.</p>',
      '<h2>They Care About More Than Just Clean Water</h2><p>Modern pool care balances effectiveness with environmental responsibility through precise chemical dosing and eco-friendly alternatives. Ask potential companies about their chemical minimization strategies and whether they use environmentally conscious products and practices.</p>',
    ],
